I sit here..  reading, crying.. remembering our allegiance.. our niavete.. our &quot;duty&quot; as Americans. Shortly after I came home,I was in a Bar.. trying to wash it away.. Someone hit me from behind.. then Spit and called me Baby killer.. Next thing I remember I was in Jail.. charged with felonious assault. Judge asked me what was my intent.. I didnt know what he was referring to.. he asked again.. what was your intent with Mr. &quot;Smith&quot;. Your Honor, I dont remember.. but it was obvious my intent was to kill him. I just acted.. there was no thought involved.. (I was 47 days out of the Corps and 61 days back from country.)Judge then said you are too violent and a menace to the Society. I tried to argue that it was reaction.. not malice....  State Prison ..  6 months to Life.....  I did my time.. Paid my debt.. but now.. when I try for decent Jobs.. the question arises.. are you now or have you ever been convicted.. I am an honest Man.. so I tell them.. and the response is always the same.. they arent  hiring.. we just filled the position.. etc etc.. The Pain lingers... just under the cuff.. forever.. I will never be able to get out from the shadow.. for it has affected us all in ways that have no words.. our hearts are broken, our minds twisted... because we did what our country asked of us.. I love this Country.. not the gov't..we trusted them.. and they disowned us.. Then and now.. People want it buried.. dont talk about it and it will go away.. avoid him.. he is a Baby killer from Vietnam.<br>
We were shit on when we were sent over and shit on when we came home.. <br><br>
Some days its almost worth taking the round..
